  exerciseName: TutorialStages
  exerciseTitle: Tutorial Stages
  exerciseText: 'Write the logic to handle Tutorial Stages, to go to the next one
    until the last.

    On the last stage it should stay there.

'
  hintText: You can do math with enum values, you can increment them.
  solutionText: "public void StartTutorial() {\r\n    // Start the tutorial on stage
    _1\r\n    tutorialStage = TutorialStage.TutorialStage_1;\r\n}\r\n\r\npublic void
    GoToNextTutorialStage() {\r\n    // Do the logic to go to the next tutorial,
    stay on the last stage\r\n    if (tutorialStage == TutorialStage.TutorialStage_COMPLETED)
    {\r\n        return;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    tutorialStage++;\r\n}"
  completedText: In this exercise you learned another extremely powerful use for
    enums, handling tutorial stages.
